an Melayu]]''\n| [[Ahmad Zahid Hamidi]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 120<br><small>(under BN)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 20.90%\n| {{Composition bar|54|222|{{United Malays National Organisation/meta/color}}}}\n| {{Composition bar|39|114|{{United Malays National Organisation/meta/color}}}}\n|-\n| [[File:Flag of the Malaysian Chinese Association.svg|60px]]\n| style=\"background:{{Malaysian Chinese Association/meta/color}};\"|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''MCA'''\n| [[Malaysian Chinese Association]]<br>{{small|''Persatuan Cina Malaysia''}}\n| [[Conservatism]]\n| [[Wee Ka Siong]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 39<br><small>(under BN)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 5.41%\n| {{Composition bar|1|222|{{Malaysian Chinese Association/meta/color}}}}\n| {{Composition bar|2|114|{{Malaysian Chinese Association/meta/color}}}}\n|-\n| [[File:Malaysian Indian Congress Flag.svg|border|60px]]\n| style=\"background:{{Malaysian Indian Congress/meta/color}};\"|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''MIC'''\n| [[Malaysian Indian Congress]]<br>{{small|''Kongres India Malaysia''}}\n| [[Social conservatism]]\n| [[Vigneswaran Sanasee]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 9<br><small>(under BN)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1.38%\n| {{Composition bar|2|222|{{Malaysian Indian Congress/meta/color}}}}\n| {{Composition bar|1|114|{{Malaysian Indian Congress/meta/color}}}}\n|-\n| [[File:Parti Pribumi Bersatu Malaysia Flag.svg|60px]]\n| style=\"background:{{Malaysian United Indigenous Party/meta/color}};\" |\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |'''BERSATU'''\n| [[Malaysian United Indigenous Party]]<br>{{small|''Parti Pribumi Bersatu Malaysia''}}\n|''[[Ketuanan Melayu]]''\n| [[Muhyiddin Yassin]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 52<br><small>(under PH)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 5.95%\n| {{Composition bar|13|222|{{Malaysian United Indigenous Party/meta/color}}}}\n| {{Composition bar|33|114|{{Malaysian United Indigenous Party/meta/color}}}}<small>(Muhyiddin Bloc)\n|-\n| [[File:PAS 